## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of data and the inherent complexity of terrorism as a subject. The lack of a universally accepted definition of terrorism complicates the analysis. Additionally, the reliance on secondary sources may introduce biases inherent in the original research. Further empirical studies are needed to deepen the understanding of the individual and collective motivations behind terrorism.

